{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"231f7bc6-00e8-40d8-a687-fdaf02981258","content":"Here's what I found:\n\n**`my_app/views.py:3`** — `datetime.now()`\n```python\nnow = datetime.now()\n```\n\nThis is **untestable** because `datetime.now()` is a static call you can't easily mock or control in tests.\n\n### Recommended fix\n\nUse Django's `django.utils.timezone.now` instead — it's a function reference that's trivially patchable:\n\n```python\nfrom django.utils import timezone\n\ndef index(request):\n    now = timezone.now()\n    return render(request, 'index.html', {'time': now})\n```\n\nIn tests you can then freeze time easily:\n\n```python\nfrom unittest.mock import patch\nfrom django.utils import timezone\n\nwith patch('my_app.views.timezone.now', return_value=some_fixed_datetime):\n    ...\n```\n\nThis was a small project — only **1 file / 1 occurrence** found. No other untestable statics (`utcnow()`, `date.today()`, `time.time()`, `uuid.uuid4()`, `random.*`) were detected. Want me to apply the fix?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ec7450d7-0a08-4a8c-a796-6226ef17bc1b","outputTokens":271,"requestId":"0429:1256A4:1CAD6CE:20ADB9F:69E83393"},"id":"faa3a862-d83f-48a3-a55f-4357cfb2c850","timestamp":"2026-04-22T02:34:00.985Z","parentId":"88d989b1-895c-4873-b631-d71632c079af"}
